fix: eliminate cors/no-cors double-downloads for decoration and OS assets

Root cause: same-origin files fetched in both no-cors (<img>) and cors
(fetch/TextureLoader) modes use different HTTP-cache keys, causing
production re-downloads even with immutable Cache-Control headers.

Parent (index.html):
- Add PARENT_DECORATION_ASSETS list (reflection.png, shimmer.png) as
  single source of truth for parent decoration textures
- Prewarm both into __modelAssetCache via __prewarmBlob at startup
- Set THREE.DefaultLoadingManager.setURLModifier to resolve all
  default-manager TextureLoader calls through __cachedModelUrl (auto-
  dedupes any future texture added to the list)
- Focus shimmer <img> and predecodeCriticalAssets now use __cachedModelUrl
  to share the prewarmed blob instead of issuing a second fetch

OS (OS/index.html):
- cacheImage now delegates to getOrCreateBlobUrl (shared in-flight map,
  fixes eager/lazy race condition)
- All start-menu and showcase-layer icon injections wrapped in deferIconImgSrc
- Static <img src> for paint tools, video loader, messenger icon, notification
  avatar converted to data-blob-src
- Dynamic innerHTML fragments with same-origin <img> wrapped in deferIconImgSrc
- Template-patch else branch now rewrites uncached srcs to data-blob-src
  instead of leaving raw src (which bypassed the blob cache entirely)
- bootscreen.svg removed from EXTRA_ASSETS eager preload (direct-DOM <img>
  at parse time; eager cors fetch caused a second download)

Docs: asset-deduplication.md gets cors/no-cors gotcha section, updated
Mechanism A+B notes, new Mechanism E (parent decoration pipeline), and a
Golden rules checklist. new-chat-context.md cross-links it as must-read.